<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../media/EN_TV_003.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><b>Adventures Down Under</b></font></p><p align="left">Discover a land of contrasts. From luxuriant tropical scenery to vast tracts of arid <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q1" type="droptarget" />, from terraced vineyards to snow-clad ski slopes, from towering mountain peaks to deep rocky <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q2" type="droptarget" /></font>, from cool alpine streams to salt and freshwater <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q3" type="droptarget" /></font>, from small mountain villages to vibrant cosmopolitan cities - Australia has something for everyone.</font></p><p align="left">Explore the lush green interior of the tropical <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q4" type="droptarget" /> of Queensland - home to hundreds of species of plants, birds, mammals and reptiles. Admire spectacular <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q5" type="droptarget" /></font> as they cascade into tranquil pools of crystal-clear water. Relax on the soft white sands of world-renowned <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q6" type="droptarget" /></font>, go snorkelling or scuba diving on the Great Barrier Reef, the world's largest living organism, or take a cruise around the beautiful desert <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q7" type="droptarget" /></font> that lie just off the east <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q8" type="droptarget" /></font>.</font></p><p align="left">Go horse riding in the Blue Mountains of New South Wales. As you meander along towering <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q9" type="droptarget" /> tops, enjoy breathtaking views of the fertile river <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q10" type="droptarget" /></font> below. Stop for a picnic along the way and taste fresh produce from some of Australia's most productive <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q11" type="droptarget" /></font>.</font></p><p align="left">Go climbing or skiing in the Snowy Mountains - Australia's highest <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q12" type="droptarget" /> and the country's winter sports playground. </font></p><p align="left">Go canoeing or water skiing or take a cruise on Australia's longest <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q13" type="droptarget" />, the Murray, as it wends its way from its source high in the Snowy Mountains to Encounter Bay in South Australia, where it flows into the Indian <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q14" type="droptarget" /></font>.</font></p><p align="left">Visit Mount Gambier, just one of the many extinct <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q15" type="droptarget" /> in South Australia, and enjoy stunning views of the surrounding countryside from the crater. </font></p><p align="left">Or visit a World Heritage site - two <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q16" type="droptarget" /> jutting out into Shark Bay in Western Australia, where the action centres on a group of dolphins that have a taste for human contact.</font></p><p align="left"><font size="2"></font></p>
